This paper focuses on accelerating join operations in modern database systems, which is a core topic in the field of database management. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Hadoop and Map-Reduce, which are commonly used in distributed computing and big data processing, suggesting that cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of GPU acceleration, which is a common technique in high-performance computing, suggesting that cs.PF (Performance) is a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for estimating the number of results and allocating storage space, which is related to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
